> GENERAL MGR, CONSTRUCTION SVCS
>
> ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS: This position will be a part of the Construction
> Management Services group at Enron Facility Services. Enron Facility
> Services has separate benefit programs from Enron Corp. The General
Manager
> is responsible for the successful completion of all construction
associated
> with energy projects within the Southeast Region. The GM is responsible
for
> the profit and loss of the regional office, staffing and training of
> personnel, and identification and development of new business within the
> region. The GM must be able to simultaneously manage multiple Construction
> Managers and office personnel, as well as deal effectively with EFS, EES
> and with outside customers at a high level. Responsibilities: Write and
> implement the Business Plan for the Southeast Regional office. Hire and
> train qualified personnel to manage project construction and office
> functions. Hire origination and project development personnel to pursue
new
> business outside of EES projects. Build and maintain a working
relationship
> with EFS, EES and outside clients. Maintain a good relationship with all
> inside and outside subcontractors, ensure that subcontractors maintain
> budget and schedule constraints.
>
>
> ESSENTIAL REQUIREMENTS: BSME/EE or Construction Management. Minimum of
> seven to ten years of field construction experience, and the ability to
run
> a regional office. Knowledge of electrical, HVAC, boiler retrofits,
> controls, hot water and condensate systems. Experience in managing
> successful construction projects. Knowledge of the construction process,
> scheduling, resource allocation, budgeting and cash flow processing.
> Ability to work well as a team player and to communicate effectively with
> others.
>
>
> PREFERRED SKILLS: NA.
>
>
> SPECIAL CHARACTERISTICS: NA.
>
>
> CONTACT: As an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer, we are
> committed to diversity in our workforce. Interested candidates, please
send
> your resumes via email (preferred) to eesjobs4@enron.com for
consideration.
> Resumes may also be mailed to Enron Facility Services, P. O. Box 1188,
> Houston, TX 77251-1188, Attn: EESJOBS4, EB1010a, or faxed to 713-646-8095.
> Please be sure to indicate Job ID#: 109211 in your subject line or cover
> letter. PLEASE DO NOT CONTACT THE RECRUITER OR HIRING MANAGER.
>
>
